<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

Background data on legionellosis in Italy.
-----------------------------------------
The first case of legionellosis in Italy was reported in 1981 (from Emilia
Romagna). Passive surveillance was initiated in 1983. 21 cases were
confirmed from May to Dec 1983. 819 presumptive cases and 490 confirmed
cases were registered from 1983 to Mar 1994 -- 62.6 per cent from northern
Italy.
Year / Cases / Remarks
1994 / 148 / 45.3 per cent from Lombardia
1995 / 135 / 40.7 per cent from Lombardia
1996 / 128
1997 / 93 / 30.0 per cent from Lombardia and 22.2 per cent from Piemonte
1998 / 129 / 17 per cent fatal -- 44.9 per cent from Piemonte and 23.4 per
cent from Lombardia
1999 / 239 / 8.7 per cent fatal - 27.6 per cent from Piemonte and 36.0 per
cent from Lombardia
2000 / 60
2001 / 300
2002 / 293
Rates per 100 000: 0.18 in 1998; 0.405 in 1999.
7 cases were reported among tourists in Rome during 1998 to 1999; 10 in
2000. The male/female ratio for reported cases is 3.45/1, and 56.6 per cent
of the patients are above age 49.
Seropositivity rates (1996) are 2.7 per cent in Campania and 3.8 per cent
in Calabria.
Notable outbreaks:
1980 -- An outbreak (21 cases) was reported at a hotel in Como.
2002 -- An outbreak (6 cases, 1 fatal) was reported among pilgrims to San
Giovanni Rotondo (Puglia region).
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
